isValidColoring

boolean isValidColoring
True if the GCPIndividual is a valid coloring (ie not neighboring edges are the same color) of the give graph. False if any two neighboring nodes are the same color.

Constructor Detail

GCPIndividual

public GCPIndividual()
Calls the factory for the standard Individual and then sets the maxColor to some random value less than or equal to the number of nodes in the phenotype Graph.

Method Detail

calcFitness

protected double calcFitness()
Iterates over the individuals to count the number of invalid edges then sets if the coloring is valid or not. Returns the fitness as the difference of the max color of the GCPIndividual the number of invalid edges divided (both normalized) and subtracted from one.

Specified by:
calcFitness in class malthus.Individual
Returns:
The fitness of a solution.

reproduce

public GCPIndividual reproduce(malthus.Individual mate)
Creates a new GCPIndividual using the Individual factory, setting the max color to that of the calling parent. The child's genotype is then set to the result of the crossover of both parents and then mutates the child.

Overrides:
reproduce in class malthus.Individual
Returns:
The product of crossover and mutation from the two parent individuals.
